{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review the Care Leaver Strategy and implement opportunity-based changes.",
        "additional_details": "Having spent a large time of my life in the care of the local authority I am saddened but unfortunately not shocked at the unnecessary hurdles that care leavers and looked after children face compared to their peers. I currently face the prospect of losing my accommodation post-21 despite the fact I am in full - time further education. My LA are no longer obliged to pay costs. Housing is obsimal and neglectful. The statistical outcomes for care leavers are shocking\r\n\r\nThis has to change.\r\n\r\nNow.",
        "background": "We want the Government to review the care leavers strategy and consider implementing:\r\n- Extending the age of housing support/funding for those in education to 25\r\n- Making care leaver housing providers more accountable for shortcomings in accommodation",
